---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import CTASection from '../../components/CTASection';
import Reviews from '../../components/Reviews';
import ServiceForm from '../../components/ServiceForm';
import LicenseBadges from '../../components/LicenseBadges.astro';
import BrandsSection from '../../components/BrandsSection.astro';

const faqSchemaObject = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How quickly can you get to Anaheim for AC repair?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "We dispatch same-day across Anaheim. Most calls are answered within a few hours."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you offer free estimates in Anaheim?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes — free estimates and free diagnostics with any approved repair for Anaheim homeowners."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What areas of Anaheim do you serve?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "All of Anaheim including Anaheim Hills, Downtown Anaheim, and surrounding neighborhoods."
      }
    }
  ]
};
---

<BaseLayout title="HVAC Services in Anaheim, CA | HiLo Heating & Air" description="Expert HVAC repair, AC installation, and heating services in Anaheim, CA. Same-day service from licensed technicians serving Anaheim and Orange County since 2000." faqSchema={faqSchemaObject}>
  <Header />
  <main>
    <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-brand-blue to-blue-800 py-20 sm:py-28">
      <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-white mb-4">AC Repair Anaheim CA</h1>
        <p class="text-white/80 text-lg max-w-2xl mx-auto">Because sweating through summer isn't an option. A lot of AC problems are actually pretty simple fixes — when you call the right people.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-10 pb-4 sm:py-16 sm:pb-6 bg-white">
      <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <LicenseBadges />
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-6 lg:gap-10 items-start">
          <div>
            <span class="inline-block bg-brand-blue/10 text-brand-blue text-sm font-semibold px-4 py-1.5 rounded-full mb-4">Schedule Service</span>
            <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-brand-blue mb-4">Get a Free Estimate</h2>
            <p class="text-slate-600 mb-6">Fill out the form and our team will get back to you within 15 minutes. Same-day service available.</p>
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand-blue/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center">
                  <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-brand-blue" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 6v6h4.5m4.5 0a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/></svg>
                </div>
                <span class="text-sm font-semibold text-brand-blue">Same-Day Service Available</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand-blue/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center">
                  <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-brand-blue" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12.75L11.25 15 15 9.75m-3-7.036A11.959 11.959 0 013.598 6 11.99 11.99 0 003 9.749c0 5.592 3.824 10.29 9 11.623 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.31-.21-2.571-.598-3.751h-.152c-3.196 0-6.1-1.248-8.25-3.285z"/></svg>
                </div>
                <span class="text-sm font-semibold text-brand-blue">Free Diagnostics with Repair</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand-blue/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center">
                  <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-brand-blue" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M2.25 18.75a60.07 60.07 0 0115.797 2.101c.727.198 1.453-.342 1.453-1.096V18.75M3.75 4.5v.75A.75.75 0 013 6h-.75m0 0v-.375c0-.621.504-1.125 1.125-1.125H20.25M2.25 6v9m18-10.5v.75c0 .414.336.75.75.75h.75m-1.5-1.5h.375c.621 0 1.125.504 1.125 1.125v9.75c0 .621-.504 1.125-1.125 1.125h-.375m1.5-1.5H21a.75.75 0 00-.75.75v.75m0 0H3.75m0 0h-.375a1.125 1.125 0 01-1.125-1.125V15m1.5 1.5v-.75A.75.75 0 003 15h-.75M15 10.5a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm3 0h.008v.008H18V10.5zm-12 0h.008v.008H6V10.5z"/></svg>
                </div>
                <span class="text-sm font-semibold text-brand-blue">Upfront Pricing, No Hidden Fees</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <ServiceForm client:load />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-16 sm:py-24 bg-white">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 prose prose-lg">
        <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-brand-blue mt-0 mb-4">AC & Heating Services in Anaheim</h2>

        <p>Here's something most HVAC companies won't admit: a lot of AC problems are actually pretty simple fixes. A bad capacitor. A refrigerant top-off. A clogged drain line. Nothing dramatic — just something that needs attention before it turns into something that does become dramatic.</p>
        <p>At HiLo Heating & Air Conditioning, we've been doing <strong>ac repair Anaheim CA</strong> homeowners can rely on since 2000. That's over two decades of showing up in Anaheim summers — which, if you've lived here any length of time, you know are no joke. We've worked on basically every system type, every brand, and every kind of "my AC is doing this weird thing" scenario you can imagine.</p>
        <p>And here's our honest philosophy: if we can fix it, we fix it. We're not going to try to sell you a new system when yours just needs a repair.</p>

        <h2>When Should You Call for AC Repair in Anaheim?</h2>
        <p>Most people wait longer than they should. They notice something feels a little off — the house isn't quite as cool as it used to be, or the system seems to be running nonstop — and they figure it'll sort itself out. It usually doesn't.</p>
        <p>These are the things that typically mean your system needs a look:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Warm or lukewarm air coming through vents when the thermostat is set to cool</li>
          <li>Noises that weren't there before — banging, grinding, clicking, squealing</li>
          <li>The AC cycles on and off every few minutes without settling the temperature</li>
          <li>Your electricity bill jumped and nothing else changed</li>
          <li>There's moisture or pooling water near the unit</li>
          <li>Certain rooms just never cool down no matter what you set the thermostat to</li>
          <li>Something smells off — musty, burnt, or stale when the system kicks on</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Any one of those is worth a call. Caught early, most of these are inexpensive fixes. Left alone, they tend to snowball.</p>

        <h2>What We Handle</h2>
        <p>For <strong>ac repair in Anaheim</strong>, our technicians cover the full range — refrigerant leaks and recharges, compressor issues, capacitor and contactor replacements, fan motor repairs, frozen evaporator coils, thermostat problems, duct leaks, drainage issues. We work on all the major brands: Carrier, Trane, Lennox, Goodman, Rheem, York, and plenty of others.</p>
        <p>We carry parts in our vehicles so we're not wasting your time making multiple trips. Most repairs get handled in a single visit.</p>

        <h2>What Makes HiLo Different — Honestly</h2>
        <p>We're a local Anaheim-area company, not a franchise. There's no script we're following, no sales quota we're trying to hit. When one of our technicians comes to your home for <strong>ac repair Anaheim CA</strong> service, they're going to tell you what's actually going on — not what sounds most profitable.</p>
        <p>A few things our customers mention pretty consistently:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>We show up when we say we will.</li>
          <li>We explain what we found and what it costs before doing anything.</li>
          <li>We don't manufacture urgency or push you toward replacements you don't need.</li>
          <li>And we back our work with warranties, so if something isn't right, we make it right.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>That's really it. No gimmicks. Just solid <strong>ac repair in Anaheim</strong> from people who take the work seriously.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    

    <Reviews client:visible />
    <BrandsSection />

    <section class="py-16 sm:py-24 bg-slate-50">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-blue mb-8">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-brand-blue/10">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-brand-blue mb-2">My AC runs constantly but the house stays warm. Is that an ac repair Anaheim CA situation or a replacement?</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">Almost always repairable. A system that runs but doesn't cool is usually dealing with low refrigerant, a dirty coil, or airflow blockage — none of which require a new unit. We'll check it out and be straight with you about what we find.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-brand-blue/10">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-brand-blue mb-2">What's a ballpark cost for ac repair in Anaheim?</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">Genuinely depends on the problem. Smaller fixes like a capacitor or thermostat swap are on the lower end. Something like a compressor is more involved and costs more. We quote everything upfront — you'll know the number before we start any work.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-brand-blue/10">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-brand-blue mb-2">How fast do you respond?</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">Same-day in most cases, especially mid-summer when we know people really need it. Call (714) 853-5534 and we'll tell you exactly when we can get there.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-brand-blue/10">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-brand-blue mb-2">My system is 10 years old. Worth repairing or time to replace?</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">Ten years is middle-aged for an AC unit — not old. Whether it's worth repairing depends on what's wrong and what the repair costs relative to the system's remaining life. We'll give you that honest breakdown without steering you either way for our own benefit.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-brand-blue/10">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-brand-blue mb-2">Do you work on all AC brands?</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">Yes — Carrier, Trane, Lennox, Goodman, Rheem, York, and more. If you have a less common brand, just call and ask. Chances are we've worked on it.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-brand-blue/10">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-brand-blue mb-2">I tried fixing it myself and now it's worse. Can you still help?</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">Absolutely, and you wouldn't be the first. Electrical components and refrigerant systems are tricky — we'll assess where things stand and get it sorted out.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-brand-blue/10">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-brand-blue mb-2">Why does my AC smell weird when it turns on?</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">Musty usually means mold or mildew somewhere in the system or ductwork. Burning smells can point to electrical issues. Neither one should be brushed off — book an ac repair Anaheim CA visit and we'll track down the source.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-brand-blue/10">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-brand-blue mb-2">How do I keep from needing repairs so often?</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">Annual maintenance — ideally every spring before you really need the AC. It's not glamorous advice, but a tune-up catches the small stuff before it turns into a breakdown in July. Ask us about our maintenance options.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-brand-blue/10">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-brand-blue mb-2">What areas do you cover near Anaheim?</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">We serve most of Orange County — Fullerton, Garden Grove, Orange, Santa Ana, Buena Park, Placentia, and nearby communities. Give us a call to confirm your area.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-brand-blue/10">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-brand-blue mb-2">How do I schedule ac repair in Anaheim with HiLo?</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">Call (714) 853-5534 or go to hiloheatingandair.com. We'll find a time that works for you, get someone out there, and make sure things are actually fixed — not just temporarily patched — before we leave.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="bg-brand-blue/5 py-8">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
        <p class="text-brand-blue font-semibold">HiLo Heating & Air Conditioning · 8131 Electric Ave, Stanton, CA 90680, United States</p>
        <p class="text-slate-600 mt-1"><a href="tel:+17148535534" class="hover:text-brand-red transition">(714) 853-5534</a> · <a href="mailto:info@hiloheatingandair.com" class="hover:text-brand-red transition">info@hiloheatingandair.com</a></p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <CTASection client:visible />
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
